President Obama has announced his intent to nominate Leslie R. Caldwell as the Assistant Attorney General for the Criminal Division at the Department of Justice. Caldwell is currently a partner at Morgan Lewis & Bockius LLP and has extensive experience in corporate investigations and white-collar practice. She has previously served as Director of the DOJ Enron Task Force and has received various awards for her work. Caldwell holds a B.A. in Economics from Pennsylvania State University and a J.D. from George Washington University Law School.

Additionally, President Obama plans to nominate Richard Stengel as the Under Secretary for Public Diplomacy and Public Affairs at the Department of State. Stengel is currently the Managing Editor of Time Magazine and has held various positions in journalism, including being a Senior Adviser and Chief Speechwriter for Bill Bradley's Presidential campaign. He has also worked with Nelson Mandela on his autobiography. Stengel received a B.A. from Princeton University and was a Rhodes Scholar at the University of Oxford.